Singer Innocent Idibia aka 2baba has said he will never stop celebrating late musician Olanrewaju Fasasi, popularly known as Sound Sultan who died on July 11. Sound Sultan died after battling Angioimmunoblastic T-Cell Lymphoma. He has since been buried in New Jersey in the United States of America. The singer who died at the age of 44 is survived by his wife, three children and siblings. Sharing on Instagram days after the singer’s death, 2baba promised to keep the family he left behind safe. He wrote, “Couldn’t bring myself to do this but what can we do. Rest well. Till we meet again my dear friend and brother. “Still so unreal. “Will never stop celebrating u. I promise u your fam will be safe and good. #GRATEFUL for u and the blessings that u represented in my life.” 2baba and Sound Sultan have songs together e.g Bush Meat, Enter The Place, Prayer etc.